{
  "stem": "10181.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, well we weren't yet together, but I'll make it quick because, you know, it's-- what happened was that, after a while, I was put in the same hospital as my sister, and after about a month.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then the nuns said I-- you know, said I should go to synagogue, I should pray.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, they didn't try to convert me or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I remember them taking me to synagogue once in Maastricht and [? during ?] I was-- I got-- I didn't feel well, so they took me back.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But anyway, after two months in the hospital, we were ready to leave-- but where to?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't know where to send us, because we were in the way often.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't know whether anybody was left alive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We knew our mother had gone to England, but we hadn't heard anything from her after all those years, so we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We assumed she was OK.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So first-- first thing they wanted to do--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first thing they wanted to do was to register us, you know, like returning citizens, you know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that's when we registered with the Dutch authorities, or whatever they were at the time, and they-- the guy registering us was one of those real civil servants, and they said, wait a minute-- you were born Dinslaken, Germany.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You came to Holland 1938.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You're not Dutch.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You're DP, you know, displaced person.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I have to send you back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So of course, we said no way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course the nuns also said, no way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They wouldn't-- they would never-- see, they said, even if it means we have to take a hospital bed, and we shouldn't, we're not going to allow them to-- we're not gonna let them free.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We're not-- not releasing them from the hospital if they have to be sent back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then, they came to an agreement with these-- with this people and-- and-- who registered us to take us out of the hospital and put us for a few days in-- in a school where some other Dutch non-Jewish children who were kept there for some reason or other, but we were free to go out whenever we wanted to.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went, you know, restricted.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we spent most of our day visiting the various-- they were very friendly, those nuns, so we went to visit them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had nothing really to do.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then, they were just sort of trying to find a solution for us, the nuns, that [INAUDIBLE] in the hospital.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They heard that this same gentleman who had taken care was arrested, that Berenbaum was coming.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't know that they had been with him, of course, but they heard that somebody had come back who had been on a different train with us-- than us.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, and also been taken out of-- he had been in Bergen-Belsen, and he had been on a different train, liberated by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And two months, you know, after liberation, they came finally back to Holland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was June-- was July, I think, yeah, July in 1945.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was going through Maastricht on his way to Amsterdam, and he had some orphans with us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So then the-- the nuns asked, would you mind going with them?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's a good-- yes, of course not, we know him, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Oh, that's good.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were reunited with them and with their children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, with their-- their children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had some other orphans with them, but we really didn't-- these were not people that had been with us in Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't know them, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We may have known one or two of them from-- from Bergen-Belsen, but I don't really remember whether we knew them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They took us on-- on trucks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were taken by Americans to Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then from Amsterdam, we were taken to a little town called Laren, where there was a Jewish orphanage of sort of kids who had survived, or in hiding, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this is probably where he went with his children for the time being.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in the meanwhile, this uncle, Adolf, who had disappeared right at the very beginning, had been in hiding all through the war.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He had managed to elude the Germans, and he was looking for us because he had seen on a Red Cross list that we had survived.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he didn't know where we were, so then somebody told him, maybe they're in Maastricht.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
